 The People’s Democratic Party ( PDP) Presidential candidate will on Wednesday get his certificate of returns. Atiku who defeated 11 other aspirants to clinch the party’s ticket ahead of the 2023 Presidential election, is billed to be presented with his certificate of returns, according to a statement by Debo Ologunagba, the party’s national publicity secretary. Ologunagba in the statement on behalf of the National Working Committee of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), invited all Governors, Governorship Candidates, Presidential aspirants, members of the Board of Trustees belonging to the party. Others invited to the event billed for the party’s national secretariat, Wadata Plaza, Abuja, are members of the National Assembly, all other Candidates of the Party and all critical stakeholders. According to the party, the Special Ceremony of the Presentation of Certificate of Return to the PDP Presidential Flag bearer, will take place at the headquarters by 12 noon. Read also: Atiku will revive Nigeria’s economy- Ortom It will be recalled that soon after his victory, the PDP flag bearer, after his victory went ahead to commence the process of reconciliation, with a promised to cooperate and work with all the party members and give them a sense of belonging. The former Vice President expressed his willingness and readiness, to carry everyone along even as he pleaded with grievances members of the party to use the party’s machinery to resolve all grievances. “Once again I want to extend my commendation to the leadership to our party, the governors who have worked day and night to ensure that this convention is a success, that we will continue to work to make the party stronger and stronger”